{"title":"{{< i18n risk_register >}}","markdown":{"headingText":"{{< i18n risk_register >}}","headingAttr":{"id":"sec-risk-register","classes":[],"keyvalue":[]},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n## Purpose of This Document\n\nThis Risk Register provides the **complete and authoritative list of project\nrisks**, including:\n\n- Risk identification and categorization\n- Probability and impact assessment\n- Risk exposure level\n- Ownership\n- Associated KPIs and Stage‑Gates\n\nThis document is a **mandatory PMBOK artifact** and is the primary input to the\n**Risk Response Plan**.\n\n---\n\n## Risk Scoring Methodology\n\n### Probability Scale\n\n- Low (L)\n- Medium (M)\n- High (H)\n\n### Impact Scale\n\n- Low (L)\n- Medium (M)\n- High (H)\n- Very High (VH) — reserved for ecological risk\n\n### Risk Exposure\n\nDerived qualitatively from Probability × Impact and used for prioritization:\n\n- Low\n- Medium\n- High\n- **Critical** (ecological priority)\n\n---\n\n## Detailed Risk Register (Full Table)\n\n| ID | Description | Cat. | Prob. | Impact | Exposure | Primary KPI | Stage-Gate | Risk Owner | Notes |\n|----|-------------------------------|-----|:---:|:---:|:---:|:---:|------------|------------|------|\n| R1 | Automated screening incorrectly excludes benthic‑relevant imagery (false negatives) | Environmental / Ecological | M | **VH** | **Critical** | KPI‑3 | G1, G2, G3, G4 | Environmental SME Lead | Primary ecological risk |\n| R2 | Annotation subjectivity leads to inconsistent ecological labeling | Environmental / Data | H | H | High | KPI‑4 | G1, G2 | Environmental SME Lead | Requires consensus process |\n| R3 | Model fails to meet minimum ecological performance thresholds | Technical | M | H | High | KPI‑3 | G2 | Data Science Lead | MVP risk accepted within limits |\n| R4 | Severe class imbalance biases model behavior | Data | H | M | High | KPI‑3 | G2 | Data Science Lead | Expected, mitigable |\n| R5 | Poor image quality (turbidity, lighting, backscatter) reduces screening reliability | Data / Operational | H | M | High | KPI‑3 | G2, G3 | Data Engineering Lead | Environmental conditions driven |\n| R6 | Delays in environmental SME availability | Operational | M | H | High | KPI‑2 | G1, G2 | Project Manager | Direct schedule risk |\n| R7 | Misalignment between technical and ecological expectations | Governance | M | H | High | KPI‑3 | G1, G2 | Project Manager | Requires frequent checkpoints |\n| R8 | Over‑automation reduces expert trust in outputs | Operational / Adoption | M | M | Medium | KPI‑1 | G3 | Product Owner | Human‑in‑the‑loop critical |\n| R9 | Stakeholder resistance to adopting AI‑assisted workflows | Organizational | M | M | Medium | KPI‑6 | G3 | Product Owner | Change management risk |\n| R10 | Licensing or framework compliance issues | Compliance | L | H | Medium | — | G1 | IT / Legal | Preventive control |\n| R11 | Insufficient compute or storage resources | Technical / Infra | L | M | Low | KPI‑2 | G1 | IT / Infra | Mitigable |\n| R12 | Loss of traceability or auditability of datasets | Governance / Data | L | H | Medium | KPI‑5 | G3, G4 | Data Governance | Impacts reuse |\n| R13 | Inability to generalize across fields | Technical / Ecological | M | H | High | KPI‑4 | G3 | Data Science Lead | Blocks scaling |\n| R14 | Scope creep toward non‑MVP objectives | Governance | M | M | Medium | — | All | Project Manager | Controlled by WBS |\n| R15 | Environmental credibility questioned due to undocumented limitations | Ecological / Governance | L | **VH** | **Critical** | KPI‑3 | G2, G3 | Environmental SME Lead | Documentation mandatory |\n\n---\n\n## Risk Prioritization Summary\n\n### Critical Risks (Must Never Be Accepted)\n\n- R1 — Ecological data loss (false negatives)\n- R15 — Environmental credibility loss\n\n### High Risks (Must Be Mitigated)\n\n- R2, R3, R4, R5, R6, R7, R13\n\n### Medium Risks (Managed / Monitored)\n\n- R8, R9, R10, R12, R14\n\n### Low Risks\n\n- R11\n\n---\n\n## Governance Rules\n\n- **Any Critical risk automatically blocks Stage‑Gate progression**\n- Ecological risks override schedule and cost considerations\n- Risk ownership is mandatory and non‑delegable\n- All risk status changes must be logged\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to Other Risk Artifacts\n\n| Artifact | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| Risk Register | Risk identification & prioritization |\n| Risk Response Plan | Actions and contingencies |\n| Stage‑Gates | Decision enforcement |\n| KPI Framework | Continuous risk monitoring |\n\n---\n\n## Review Cadence\n\n- Weekly review by Project Manager\n- Mandatory review at every Stage‑Gate\n- Immediate escalation if KPI‑3 degrades\n\n---\n\n## Baseline and Change Control\n\nThis Risk Register is **baselined** upon approval.  \nAny addition, removal, or reclassification of risks requires formal change\ncontrol.\n\n","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"markdown"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":true,"code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-d